topic: History Workflow Series ("Literary Movements and physicists explorative search")

goals.1: Who invented the theory of relativity? (return the IRI and the label of the inventor).
goals.3: Identify the BGP for Nobel Prize
goals.4: Consider physicists born in Europe. For each european country return the number of physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics (the result set must be a list of triples country IRI, label and #physicists).
goals.5: Return the countries which won at least once all the type of Nobel Prizes with the people born there. (the result set must be a list of couples country IRI and label).
goals.6: Amongst the physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics, find who had discovered or invented at least 3 things (the result set must be a list of triples physicist IRI, label and #discoveries ).
goals.7: Amongst the physicists who won the Nobel Prize in Physics, find who taught in the university of his/her city of birth (the result set must be a list of elements of the form physicist IRI, label, university IRI and label).

startup the evaluation

look at the properties of the theory of relativity
output: The Encyclopedia of Science Fiction ID

3.narrative: Nobel Prize iun Physics is part of Nobel Prize
3.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?obj ?name WHERE { wd:Q38104 wdt:P361 ?obj . ?obj sc:name ?name. }

4.narrative:
insert the result of TASK 3 in the file
look at Nobel prize in physics winners in Europe
4.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name COUNT(?obj) AS ?winners WHERE { ?obj wdt:P166 wd:Q38104 . ?obj wdt:P19 ?city. ?city wdt:P17 ?country. ?country wdt:P30 wd:Q46. ?country sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?country ?name

5.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
look at Nobel prize winners in Europe (get the countries)
5.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name WHERE { { SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT ?n) AS ?nNobel WHERE{ ?n wdt:P361 wd:Q7191. } } { SELECT DISTINCT ?country ?name COUNT(DISTINCT ?nobel) AS ?winners WHERE { ?nobel wdt:P361 wd:Q7191. ?obj wdt:P166 ?nobel . ?obj wdt:P19 ?city. ?city wdt:P17 ?country. ?country sc:name ?name. }GROUP BY ?country ?name } FILTER (?winners = ?nNobel). }

6.narrative:
get the number of discoveries for people who won the Nobel Pize in Physics
filter only whose with at least 3 discoveries
6.query: SELECT ?person ?name COUNT(?disc) AS ?discoveries WHERE { ?disc wdt:P61 ?person . ?person wdt:P166 wd:Q38104 . ?person sc:name ?name. } GROUP BY ?person ?name HAVING(COUNT(?disc) > 2)

7.narrative:
single literal associated to an URI
look at the properties of people who won the Nobel Prize in Physics
7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?pr ?name WHERE { ?person wdt:P166 wd:Q38104 ; ?pr ?o. ?pr sc:name ?name. FILTER(!isLiteral(?o)). }
output: on focus list of Wikimedia project
patronym or matronym for this person

7.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?o ?name WHERE { ?person wdt:P166 wd:Q38104 ; wdt:P108 ?o. ?o sc:name ?name. } LIMIT 20
